KG name: TweetsKB - A Public and Large-Scale RDF Corpus of Annotated Tweets
Description: TweetsKB is a public RDF corpus of anonymized data for a large collection of annotated tweets. The dataset currently contains data for more than 1.5 billion tweets- spanning almost 5 years (January 2013 - November 2017). Metadata information about the tweets as well as extracted entities- sentiments- hashtags and user mentions are exposed in RDF using established RDF/S vocabularies. For the sake of privacy- we anonymize the usernames and we do not provide the text of the tweets. However- through the tweet IDs- actual tweet content and further information can be fetched.Links to all parts:* Part 1 (Jan 2013 - Feb 2014): https://zenodo.org/record/573852* Part 2 (Mar 2014 - Dec 2014): https://zenodo.org/record/577572* Part 3 (Jan 2015 - Oct 2015): https://zenodo.org/record/579597* Part 4 (Nov 2015 - Aug 2016): https://zenodo.org/record/579601* Part 5 (Sep 2016 - Nov 2017): https://zenodo.org/record/1095592Sample files- example queries and more information are available through TweetsKB's home page: http://l3s.de/tweetsKB/.
Languages: Could not process formulated query on indicated endpoint.
